The paper presents a concolic testing approach for Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), which involves combining program execution and symbolic analysis to explore the execution paths of a software program. This work is highly relevant to the field of machine learning, specifically in the area of DNNs, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves formalizing coverage criteria for DNNs and developing a method for increasing test coverage, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses finding adversarial examples, which suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category.
